ABUJA –  President Muhammadu Buhari has gone into meeting with security chiefs over the Shi’ites protests. SaharaReporters reports that President Muhammadu Buhari is currently holding a meeting with Nigeria’s security chiefs at the presidential villa in Abuja. The meeting follows a clash between the Nigeria Police Force and the members of the Islamic Movement in Nigeria (IMN) which happened on Monday afternoon. The meeting reportedly started at 4pm on Monday.Details later… 